"Now we have to clean up fundamentally".
The politician announced: "In the Occupational Safety and Health Act, which we want to pass in the cabinet at the end of July, there are also measures that do not only affect the meat industry - for example, higher inspection rates for occupational safety or clear criteria for community accommodation".
